# Advanced Text Formatting
## Specialized inline syntax

We cover all the text formatting elements the DSL supports, including math elements, references, and special formats.

---
layout: content
---

# Complete Text Formatting

## Combined Basic Formats
**Bold text** with *italics* and ***both combined*** plus ~~strikethrough text~~.

We can ==highlight== important text and use `inline code` anywhere.

## Scientific and Technical Formats
Text with ^superscript^ for exponents like E=mc^2^ or references^[1]^.

We also support ~subscripts~ for chemical formulas like H~2~O or CO~2~.

## Advanced Links and References
This is a [basic link](https://example.com) and this is a [link with a title](https://example.com "Descriptive title").

We can also create [![image that is a link](assets/link-icon.png)](https://example.com) where the image works as a link.

### References and Footnotes
This text has a reference[^first] and another reference[^second] that appear at the end.

[^first]: This is the first footnote with additional information.
[^second]: Second note that includes a [link](https://example.com) inside the reference.

